President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring July 17, 2018, as Made in America Day and the week of July 15 to July 21, 2018, as Made in America Week. The proclamation celebrates American manufacturing, construction, agriculture, mining, and entrepreneurship, highlighting their importance to the nation's prosperity and economic vitality. Trump emphasizes that products made in America represent the global gold standard for quality, innovation, and craftsmanship, thanks to a highly skilled workforce. He also notes that his administration has implemented historic tax cuts and reforms that have attracted investment and jobs back to the country, boosting optimism among American manufacturers. Trump pledges to continue cutting unnecessary regulations and pursuing fair and reciprocal trade practices to support American workers and businesses. The proclamation encourages all Americans to pay tribute to those who contribute to making America great, including builders, ranchers, crafters, and entrepreneurs.